{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6500f449-ca49-479f-9c0b-2e439396b569","content":"There's no repo here, so here's the general guidance for the migration:\n\n## Key change: replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console.exe`, so `VSTest@3` won't work. Use a script step instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFilePrefix=TestResults\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n## TRX reports\n\nAdd the `--logger trx` argument (shown above). Then publish them:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n## Code coverage\n\nUse `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (shown above) or, for Cobertura format:\n\n```yaml\n    arguments: >\n      ...\n      --collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n      -- DataCollectionRunSettings.DataCollectors.DataCollector.Configuration.Format=cobertura\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n## Project file changes\n\nEnsure each test project opts into the new platform:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nAnd uses MSTest **3.x+**:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n```\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Before (VSTest@3) | After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform) |\n|---|---|\n| `VSTest@3` task | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` with `command: test` |\n| Built-in TRX output | `--logger trx` argument |\n| Built-in coverage | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` argument |\n| Results auto-published | Add `PublishTestResults@2` (condition: always) |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b0045bb9-94d9-45eb-92a0-3ed62944c3aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a comprehensive answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":658,"requestId":"5C37:3CEFF5:9F009:C75F5:69F54AD3"},"id":"b9e4632d-ca14-44d9-aa90-d956cc20f00c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:52:49.454Z","parentId":"fa794a75-5bc5-412c-bc41-0b5c4fe2c2d1"}
